<p> 
This map is a choropleth map that represents the average gender gap in internet access across the world. <Br>The darker colors indicate higher internet access and the lighter gray indicates less internet access. </Br><Br>We can note that the countries with the widest gender gap are also lower-income countries.</Br>
</p>

<p> 
Closing the internet gender gap in these countries is a difficult task, but it opens the doors for new opportunities to these people and there's no question that a more connected world is also a more equal one. 
</p>


